    data_state, manual), KillSwitchStatus (frozen, scope, target_id,
    is_active, timestamps, activator, reason),
    KillSwitchActivateRequest (validation), HaltEvent (frozen, MTTH
    measurement, orders_cancelled, positions_flattened),
    EmergencyPostureDecision (frozen, posture, trigger, counts, timing).
  - libs/contracts/interfaces/kill_switch_service_interface.py — 5
    abstract methods: activate_kill_switch, deactivate_kill_switch,
    get_status, is_halted, execute_emergency_posture.
  - services/api/services/kill_switch_service.py — Full implementation:
    in-memory kill switch state registry keyed by (scope, target_id),
    MTTH measurement via monotonic clock (trigger → order cancellation
    confirmation), ordered cancellation across affected adapters.
    Emergency posture execution: flatten_all (cancel orders + close
    positions at market), cancel_open (cancel orders only), hold
    (no-op for human intervention). Scope-affects-adapter logic for
    global (all), strategy (matching strategy_id), symbol (conservative).
    Structured logging on all state changes.
  - services/api/routes/kill_switch.py — 6 endpoints:
    POST /global (200/409), POST /strategy/{id} (200/409),
    POST /symbol/{symbol} (200/409), DELETE /{scope}/{target_id} (200/404),
    GET /status (200), POST /emergency-posture/{deployment_id} (200/404).
    Module-level DI with set/get_kill_switch_service().
  - tests/unit/test_safety_contracts.py — 19 tests (enum stability,
    KillSwitchStatus/KillSwitchActivateRequest/HaltEvent/
    EmergencyPostureDecision construction, frozen, serialization).
  - tests/unit/test_kill_switch_service.py — 18 tests (activation at
    each scope, custom trigger, already-active rejection, deactivation,
    deactivate-inactive rejection, status queries, is_halted checks
    for global/strategy/symbol, MTTH measurement, emergency posture
